    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">My very dear uncle!!!</p>
            <p>Your letter and those from my dear<lb/> sisters have we all received in the<lb/> best
                health; and hope that you may<lb/> receive this rules also in the best
                situation.<lb/> Although I have read that you <sic>has</sic> been<lb/> indisposed;
                which displeased me much,<lb/> and wish you at the same time that you<lb/> are
                repaired again.</p>
            <p>Now <sic>me</sic> dear uncle I will also congratulate<lb/> you with your anniversary
                (although I am<lb/> not in your presence) My wish is than that<lb/> the Almighty
                heavenly Father preserve<lb/> you yet many years for misfortune; but that<lb/> He
                give you a series of happy days <add>אמן</add>.<lb/> I thank you also heartily that
                you give many a pleasure to <sic>me</sic> sisters; they are very<lb/> content
                    <sic>till</sic> here I hope it will be also in<lb/> the continuation. I pray you
                to take<lb/> farther care for them; be thou their father<lb/> and their conductor
                upon all their ways.<lb/> We have here no winter this year, it<lb/> has no fusen, so
                that we have not skated.</p>
            <p rend="The following lines are written sideways down the left side of the page.">P. S.
                That the cheese is to your taste<lb/> does me a great joy; eat then with a good
                appetite. Farewell and think<lb/> on me.</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>If my sisters send us their portraits in the<lb/> spring I beg you to send it also
                from you;<lb/> you shall well think they have it already<lb/> from me; but I would
                have it very willingly<lb/> for me alone, I hope that you shall not fail.<lb/> Also
                I pray thee to write me this time also<lb/> any rules, If you cannot write a great
                letter<lb/> do than me the pleasure to write a little,<lb/> I shall content with a
                few words from thee.<lb/> Now <sic>me</sic> dear uncle <sic>life</sic> happy in the
                future<lb/> kiss my sisters for me; and after having<lb/> saluted, <del>you</del>
                and having kissed thee in my<lb/> thoughts I am with the most respect</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your affectionate niece till in eternity</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Jeannette Elkus</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(center)">Geliebter Oheim!</p>
            <p>Mit freuden ergreif ich die Faden um dich auch<lb/> Zeilen zuzufügen, und hoffe daß
                die dieselben in den<lb/> Wohlstand er<add>?</add>brief, welches ich dich von meiner
                Seite<lb/> auf mittheilen kann, Du sagt vorlängst dein 59te<lb/> Jahr angetreten so
                ist meinen herzl<add>?</add>sten Wunsch<lb/> daß der liebe Gott dich noch viele
                Jahren dein<lb/>
                <add>?</add> Leben mag <add>?</add>, und <add>?</add> auch das<lb/> du viele Freude
                an meinen Mehrheiten Schonester<lb/>
                <add>?</add> beleben, nun habe wohl ge<add>?</add> Onkel und<lb/> grüße dich
                    wie<add>?</add>mahl deine <add>?</add><lb/>
                <persName role="author">Julia Elkus</persName></p>
        </body>
